## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose

This TDD specifies the technical implementation for fixing the inject overwrite bug (v1.0.4) and introducing per-file version tracking (v1.0.5) in the Kiro SDLC Agents VS Code extension. It covers architecture decisions, module design, data structures, and implementation patterns.

### 1.2 Scope

* Fix detectModifiedFiles() version-gating logic in checksum.ts
* Implement per-file workspace manifest (.kiro/.sdlc-manifest.json)
* Implement safeUpdate() with smart overwrite decision logic in injector.ts
* Implement getVersionReport() for per-file status display
* Implement migrateLegacyVersion() for backward compatibility
* Update extension.ts command registration for renamed “Show File Versions” command

### 1.3 Technology Stack

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Layer | Technology | Version |
| Language | TypeScript | 5.x |
| Runtime | Node.js | 18+ |
| Platform | VS Code Extension API | 1.85+ |
| Build Tool | npm + tsc | — |
| Packaging | vsce | latest |
| Hashing | Node.js crypto (SHA-256) | built-in |

### 1.4 Design Principles

* **Single Responsibility**: Each module handles one concern (config, checksum, injection, extension lifecycle)
* **Fail-Safe Migration**: Write new data before deleting old data
* **Idempotent Operations**: Running inject/update multiple times produces same result
* **Progressive Enhancement**: Legacy format auto-migrates without user intervention

### 1.5 Constraints

* Extension runs in VS Code’s Node.js sandbox — no native modules
* Single workspace folder only (multi-root not supported)
* File system operations must be synchronous for manifest consistency
* No network calls — all operations are local

