## 2. System Architecture

### 2.1 Architecture Overview

The extension follows a layered architecture within the VS Code extension host process. It consists of four TypeScript modules with clear separation of concerns:

* **Extension Layer** (extension.ts): Command registration, UI interaction, lifecycle management
* **Injection Layer** (injector.ts): File copy logic, update strategies, version reporting
* **Checksum Layer** (checksum.ts): Hash computation, manifest management, file status classification
* **Configuration Layer** (config.ts): Component definitions, paths, constants

![Architecture Diagram](data:image/png;base64...)

Architecture Diagram

### 2.2 Component Diagram

![Component Diagram](data:image/png;base64...)

Component Diagram

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Component | Responsibility | Technology |
| extension.ts | VS Code command registration, status bar, upgrade notification | VS Code API |
| injector.ts | File injection, safe update, version report generation | Node.js fs |
| checksum.ts | SHA-256 hashing, manifest CRUD, file status classification | Node.js crypto |
| config.ts | Component definitions, source/target path mapping | TypeScript constants |

### 2.3 Data Flow Architecture

The extension operates on two manifest files:

1. **Bundled Manifest** (resources/.sdlc-checksums.json) — read-only, shipped with extension
2. **Workspace Manifest** (.kiro/.sdlc-manifest.json) — read-write, per-workspace tracking

Data flows: - injectAll → copies files → buildManifestAfterInject → writes workspace manifest - safeUpdate → detectModifiedFiles → classifies → prompts → updates → rebuilds manifest - getVersionReport → reads both manifests → compares → generates text report

### 2.4 Communication Patterns

|  |  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| From | To | Protocol | Pattern | Description |
| extension.ts | injector.ts | Function call | Sync | Command handlers invoke injection functions |
| injector.ts | checksum.ts | Function call | Sync | Injection logic uses checksum for manifest ops |
| extension.ts | VS Code API | TypeScript API | Async | UI notifications, quick picks, output channels |
| checksum.ts | File System | Node.js fs | Sync | Read/write manifest JSON, compute file hashes |

## 3. Module Design

### 3.1 Module: checksum.ts — Per-File Version Tracking

**Implements:** UC-03, UC-04, BR-02, BR-03, BR-08, BR-11, BR-12, BR-13

#### 3.1.1 Interface Definitions

export interface ChecksumManifest {
 version: string; // Extension version (e.g., "1.0.5")
 generatedAt: string; // ISO timestamp
 files: Record<string, FileChecksum>;
}

export interface FileChecksum {
 hash: string; // SHA-256 hex digest
 version: string; // Version when file was added/updated
 injectedAt: string; // ISO timestamp
}

export interface WorkspaceManifest {
 lastUpdated: string; // ISO timestamp
 files: Record<string, WorkspaceFileEntry>;
}

export interface WorkspaceFileEntry {
 version: string; // Version when file was injected
 hash: string; // SHA-256 at injection time
 injectedAt: string; // ISO timestamp
}

export interface FileStatus {
 relativePath: string;
 workspaceVersion: string;
 bundledVersion: string;
 state: "current" | "outdated" | "modified" | "missing";
}

export interface ModifiedFile {
 relativePath: string;
 expectedHash: string;
 actualHash: string;
 injectedVersion: string;
}

#### 3.1.2 Key Functions

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Function | Input | Output | Description |
| computeFileHash(filePath) | File path | SHA-256 hex string | Reads file, computes hash |
| loadBundledManifest(extensionPath) | Extension path | ChecksumManifest or null | Loads bundled checksums |
| loadWorkspaceManifest(root) | Workspace root | WorkspaceManifest or null | Loads workspace manifest |
| saveWorkspaceManifest(root, manifest) | Root + manifest | void | Writes manifest to disk |
| getFileStatuses(root, extensionPath) | Root + ext path | FileStatus[] | Classifies all files |
| detectModifiedFiles(root, extensionPath) | Root + ext path | ModifiedFile[] | Finds hash mismatches |
| isUpgradeAvailable(root, extensionPath) | Root + ext path | boolean | Any file needs update? |
| migrateLegacyVersion(root, extensionPath) | Root + ext path | void | Migrates .sdlc-version |
| buildManifestAfterInject(root, extensionPath) | Root + ext path | void | Rebuilds manifest post-inject |

#### 3.1.3 File Status Classification Logic

For each file in bundled manifest:
 IF file missing in workspace → state = "missing"
 ELSE IF workspace version != bundled version → state = "outdated"
 ELSE IF current hash != bundled hash → state = "modified"
 ELSE → state = "current"

#### 3.1.4 v1.0.4 Bug Fix — detectModifiedFiles

**Before (buggy):**

// OLD: Version-gating caused ALL entries to be skipped
if (wsManifest.version !== bundled.version) { return []; }

**After (fixed):**

// NEW: Compare hashes directly, no version gating
for (const [relativePath, entry] of Object.entries(bundled.files)) {
 const fullPath = path.join(workspaceRoot, relativePath);
 if (!fs.existsSync(fullPath)) { continue; }
 const currentHash = computeFileHash(fullPath);
 if (currentHash !== entry.hash) {
 modified.push({ relativePath, expectedHash: entry.hash, actualHash: currentHash, injectedVersion: entry.version });
 }
}

#### 3.1.5 Migration Logic (migrateLegacyVersion)

1. Check .kiro/.sdlc-version exists → if not, return (no-op)
2. Load bundled manifest
3. Parse legacy JSON → extract version (default "1.0.0" on parse error)
4. For each file in bundled manifest:
 - If file exists in workspace → record with legacy version + current hash
5. Save new .kiro/.sdlc-manifest.json
6. Delete .kiro/.sdlc-version

**Critical safety**: Step 5 (write new) MUST complete before Step 6 (delete old).

### 3.2 Module: injector.ts — Injection & Update Logic

**Implements:** UC-01, UC-02, BR-01, BR-04, BR-05, BR-06, BR-07

#### 3.2.1 Public Functions

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Function | Description | Returns |
| injectAll(root, extensionPath) | Overwrites ALL files unconditionally | string[] (injected IDs) |
| injectSelective(root, extensionPath) | User picks components via QuickPick | string[] (injected IDs) |
| safeUpdate(root, extensionPath) | Smart update with modified-file handling | string[] (updated IDs) |
| checkStatus(workspaceRoot) | Checks which components exist | Record<string, boolean> |
| getVersionReport(root, extensionPath) | Generates per-file version report | string (formatted text) |

#### 3.2.2 safeUpdate Decision Tree

safeUpdate(root, extensionPath):
 1. migrateLegacyVersion(root, extensionPath)
 2. modified = detectModifiedFiles(root, extensionPath)
 3. IF modified.length == 0 → show "No update needed", return []
 4. statuses = getFileStatuses(root, extensionPath)
 5. outdated = statuses.filter(state == "outdated")
 6. userModified = statuses.filter(state == "modified")
 7. IF outdated.length > 0 AND userModified.length == 0:
 → forceUpdate() (auto-overwrite, no prompt)
 8. ELSE → promptUpdateWithDetails(outdated, userModified)
 → "Overwrite All" → forceUpdate()
 → "Skip Modified" → updateSkipModified()
 → "Backup & Overwrite" → updateWithBackup()
 → "Cancel" → return []

#### 3.2.3 Update Strategies

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Strategy | Function | Behavior |
| Force Update | forceUpdate() | Copies all bundled files, rebuilds manifest |
| Skip Modified | updateSkipModified() | Copies all EXCEPT user-modified files |
| Backup & Overwrite | updateWithBackup() | Backs up modified to .kiro/.sdlc-backup/{timestamp}/, then force updates |

#### 3.2.4 Version Report Format

Extension version: 1.0.5
Files: 12 current, 3 outdated, 1 modified, 0 missing

⬆️ Outdated (need update):
 .kiro/agents/sm-agent.md [v1.0.3 → v1.0.5]
 .kiro/agents/ba-agent.md [v1.0.3 → v1.0.5]

✏️ Modified by user (same version, different content):
 .kiro/agents/dev-agent.md [v1.0.5]

### 3.3 Module: config.ts — Component Definitions

**Implements:** Component registry for injection

#### 3.3.1 Component Interface

export interface Component {
 id: string; // Unique identifier
 label: string; // Display name in QuickPick
 description: string; // Description in QuickPick
 sourcePath: string; // Relative to extension resources/
 targetPath: string; // Relative to workspace root
 filter?: string[]; // Optional: only copy these items
}

#### 3.3.2 Component Registry

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Source Path | Target Path | Description |
| agents | .kiro/agents | .kiro/agents | Agent prompt files |
| steering | .kiro/steering | .kiro/steering | Steering rules |
| hooks | .kiro/hooks | .kiro/hooks | Auto-trigger hooks |
| templates | documents/templates | documents/templates | Document templates |
| indexer-config | .analysis/code-intelligence | .analysis/code-intelligence | Indexer config (filtered) |
| indexer-python | scripts/python | scripts/python | Python indexer |
| indexer-java | scripts/java | scripts/java | Java indexer |
| indexer-powershell | scripts/powershell | scripts/powershell | PowerShell indexer |
| indexer-bash | scripts/bash | scripts/bash | Bash indexer |
| indexer-nodejs | scripts/nodejs | scripts/nodejs | Node.js indexer |

### 3.4 Module: extension.ts — VS Code Integration

**Implements:** Command registration, lifecycle, UI

#### 3.4.1 Registered Commands

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Command ID | Label | Handler | Description |
| kiroSdlc.injectAll | Inject All | handleInjectAll | Full injection with confirmation |
| kiroSdlc.injectSelective | Inject Selective | handleInjectSelective | Pick components to inject |
| kiroSdlc.update | Update Agents | handleUpdate | Smart update (safeUpdate) |
| kiroSdlc.status | Show File Versions | handleStatus | Status + version report |
| kiroSdlc.runIndex | Run Indexer | handleRunIndex | Execute code intelligence indexer |

#### 3.4.2 Activation Flow

activate(context):
 1. Create status bar item (right-aligned)
 2. Register all 5 commands
 3. Update status bar (check/warning icon)
 4. checkForUpgrade(context):
 a. Get workspace root
 b. migrateLegacyVersion()
 c. isUpgradeAvailable() → if false, return
 d. Show notification: "Update available → v{X}"
 - "Update Now" → execute kiroSdlc.update
 - "Show Details" → open Output Channel with version report
 - "Later" → dismiss

#### 3.4.3 Status Bar Behavior

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Condition | Icon | Tooltip |
| All components present | $(check) SDLC Agents | “All SDLC components active” |
| Some missing | $(warning) SDLC Agents | “Some components missing — click to check” |
| No workspace | $(circle-slash) SDLC | “No workspace open” |

## 4. Data Design

### 4.1 File System Layout

workspace/
├── .kiro/
│ ├── .sdlc-manifest.json ← NEW: per-file version tracking
│ ├── .sdlc-version ← LEGACY: deleted after migration
│ ├── .sdlc-backup/ ← Created by "Backup & Overwrite"
│ │ └── {timestamp}/
│ │ └── {backed-up-files}
│ ├── agents/ ← Injected agent prompts
│ ├── steering/ ← Injected steering rules
│ └── hooks/ ← Injected hooks
├── .analysis/
│ └── code-intelligence/ ← Injected indexer
└── documents/
 └── templates/ ← Injected document templates

### 4.2 Workspace Manifest Schema

**File:** .kiro/.sdlc-manifest.json

{
 "lastUpdated": "2026-05-10T10:00:00.000Z",
 "files": {
 ".kiro/agents/sm-agent.md": {
 "version": "1.0.5",
 "hash": "a1b2c3d4e5f6...",
 "injectedAt": "2026-05-10T10:00:00.000Z"
 },
 ".kiro/steering/drawio.md": {
 "version": "1.0.5",
 "hash": "f6e5d4c3b2a1...",
 "injectedAt": "2026-05-10T10:00:00.000Z"
 }
 }
}

### 4.3 Bundled Manifest Schema

**File:** resources/.sdlc-checksums.json

{
 "version": "1.0.5",
 "generatedAt": "2026-05-10T09:00:00.000Z",
 "files": {
 ".kiro/agents/sm-agent.md": {
 "hash": "a1b2c3d4e5f6...",
 "version": "1.0.5",
