 }
 }
}

### 4.4 Legacy Version Schema (to be migrated)

**File:** .kiro/.sdlc-version

{
 "version": "1.0.3"
}

## 5. Error Handling Design

### 5.1 Error Categories

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Category | Severity | Recovery Strategy |
| Bundled manifest missing | Critical | Abort operation, show error message |
| File permission denied | Warning | Skip file, continue with others, report skipped |
| Legacy file malformed | Info | Default to version “1.0.0”, continue migration |
| No workspace open | Warning | Show error message, abort |
| Hash computation failure | Warning | Skip file, log error |

### 5.2 Error Handling Patterns

// Pattern 1: Graceful degradation (file operations)
try {
 fs.copyFileSync(src, dest);
} catch (err) {
 vscode.window.showErrorMessage(`Failed to inject ${component.id}: ${err}`);
 return false;
}

// Pattern 2: Safe defaults (manifest loading)
try {
 return JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(manifestFile, "utf-8"));
} catch {
 return null; // Caller handles null case
}

// Pattern 3: Atomic migration (write-before-delete)
saveWorkspaceManifest(workspaceRoot, wsManifest); // Step 1: Write new
fs.unlinkSync(legacyFile); // Step 2: Delete old

### 5.3 User-Facing Error Messages

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Scenario | Message | Action |
| Extension package corrupted | “Extension package may be corrupted — bundled manifest missing” | Abort |
| Permission denied | “Could not update {file}: permission denied” | Skip + continue |
| No workspace | “No workspace folder open” | Abort |

## 6. Security Design

### 6.1 Threat Model

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Threat | Risk | Mitigation |
| Malicious bundled manifest | Low (extension is local) | Manifest is part of signed VSIX package |
| Hash collision | Negligible | SHA-256 has no known practical collisions |
| Path traversal in manifest | Low | All paths are relative, resolved against workspace root |
| Backup directory exposure | Low | .sdlc-backup is in .kiro/ (typically gitignored) |

### 6.2 Data Protection

* No PII is stored in manifests (only file paths and hashes)
* No network calls — all operations are local
* File content is never transmitted or logged
* SHA-256 hashes are one-way — cannot reconstruct file content

## 7. Performance Design

### 7.1 Performance Targets

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Operation | Target | Rationale |
| Hash computation per file | < 10ms | Agent files are < 50KB |
| Full manifest rebuild | < 500ms | ~50 files × 10ms |
| Status check | < 200ms | Read 2 JSON files + compare |
| Migration | < 1s | One-time operation |

### 7.2 Optimization Decisions

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Decision | Rationale |
| Synchronous file I/O | Manifest consistency > parallelism; files are small |
| No caching of hashes | Operations are infrequent (user-triggered); always fresh |
| Limit report to 15 outdated + 10 modified | Prevent UI overflow in notification |

## 8. Testing Strategy

### 8.1 Unit Test Coverage

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Module | Key Test Scenarios |
| checksum.ts | Hash computation, manifest load/save, file classification, migration |
| injector.ts | Inject all, safe update decision tree, skip modified, backup |
| config.ts | Component registry completeness |

### 8.2 Integration Test Scenarios

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| ID | Scenario | Setup | Expected |
| IT-01 | Full inject on empty workspace | No .kiro/ directory | All files injected, manifest created |
| IT-02 | Safe update with outdated files | Workspace at v1.0.3, bundle at v1.0.5 | Auto-overwrite, manifest updated |
| IT-03 | Safe update with modified files | User edited agent file | Prompt shown with 3 options |
| IT-04 | Legacy migration | .sdlc-version exists | Manifest created, legacy deleted |
| IT-05 | Upgrade notification | isUpgradeAvailable = true | Notification shown |

### 8.3 Edge Cases

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Case | Expected Behavior |
| Empty bundled manifest | All operations return early (no files to process) |
| Workspace manifest corrupted JSON | loadWorkspaceManifest returns null → treated as fresh workspace |
| File deleted between status check and update | Skip missing file, continue |
| Concurrent VS Code windows | Each workspace has independent manifest |

