## 10. Deployment Considerations

### 10.1 Release Process

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Step | Action | Tool |
| 1 | Fix bug, commit | git |
| 2 | Tag v1.0.4 | git tag v1.0.4 |
| 3 | Implement per-file tracking | git |
| 4 | Regenerate checksums | node scripts/generate-checksums.js |
| 5 | Bump package.json to 1.0.5 | manual |
| 6 | Tag v1.0.5 | git tag v1.0.5 |
| 7 | Package VSIX | vsce package |
| 8 | Push tags | git push --tags |

### 10.2 Rollback Strategy

If v1.0.5 has issues: 1. Users can reinstall v1.0.4 VSIX 2. .sdlc-manifest.json is ignored by v1.0.4 (no harm) 3. If migration already deleted .sdlc-version, v1.0.4 treats workspace as fresh (safe)

### 10.3 Backward Compatibility

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Scenario | Behavior |
| v1.0.5 on workspace with .sdlc-version | Auto-migrates to manifest |
| v1.0.5 on workspace with no version file | Creates manifest on first inject |
| v1.0.4 on workspace with .sdlc-manifest.json | Ignores manifest (doesn’t know about it) |

## 11. Appendix

### Glossary

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Term | Definition |
| Workspace Manifest | .kiro/.sdlc-manifest.json — per-file version/hash tracking |
| Bundled Manifest | resources/.sdlc-checksums.json — expected hashes shipped with extension |
| Inject | Copy bundled resource files into user’s workspace |
| Safe Update | Update that auto-overwrites outdated files, prompts for user-modified files |
| Hash | SHA-256 digest of file content (hex-encoded) |
| Version-gating | The v1.0.3 bug where version mismatch caused all entries to be skipped |

